INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('400', '10', 'Remove from heat and pour into a mini food processor.'),
('400', '11', 'Place the buratta in the processor as well.'),
('400', '12', 'Add a pinch of salt.  Process until blended, it will still be a bit chunky.  Taste for seasoning.'),
('400', '13', 'Wipe out the small fry pan and return to low heat.'),
('400', '14', 'Add 1 TB olive oil and the panko. Cook over low heat until the panko is golden.'),
('400', '15', 'Remove the cauliflower from the oven and turn on the broiler.'),
('400', '16', 'Push all the cauliflower together, so it is all up against each other.'),
('400', '17', 'Spread the buratta mixture over the cauliflower and sprinkle with the panko.'),
('400', '18', 'Place the pan back in the oven, second rack slot from the top.  Broil until the cheese is melted and golden.'),
('401', '1', 'Combine first nine ingredients (basil through olive oil) in a jar that has a secure lid and shake the heck out of it.  Set aside.'),
('401', '2', 'Cook the beans in boiling salted water to desired doneness. Shock them in cold water to stop cooking process, and drain them completely.  Leave beans to dry on a paper towel and keep them at room temperature.'),
('401', '3', 'Separate the egg yolks from the egg whites.  Separately push whites and yolks through a strainer to get fine shreds of egg whites and fine shreds of egg yolks.'),
('401', '4', 'Artfully arrange beans among four plates.  Dot the beans on each plate with six to eight olives.'),
('401', '5', 'Drizzle two tablespoons of dressing over the beans and olives on each plate.  Sprinkle one tablespoon of egg white shreds and then one teaspoon of egg yolks shreds over each bean salad.'),
('401', '6', 'Serve with some crusty bread.'),
('402', '1', 'Slice the red onion into half rings, put them in a tupperware and cover them with water, and stick them in the fridge.  This will take some of the bite out and leave them sweet and crunchy.  After maybe 20 minutes, change the water and put them back in the fridge.'),
('402', '2', 'Coarsley chop the garlic.  Put it in a blender or processor.'),
('402', '3', 'Add the egg yolks, lemon zest and juice, orange zest (save the orange for supremes), zest from half the grapefruit and the grapefruit juice.  Also add the parmesan, anchovies, jalapeo and parsley.'),
('402', '4', 'Get the blender going and while it''s running, drizzle in the oilve oil.  let it go for a few minutes to make sure everything is well blended.'),
('402', '5', 'Pour the dressing into a container and stick it in the fridge - it''s going to be more than you need for this salad unless you are making a really big one.'),
('402', '6', 'Toast the pecans in a skillet and set them aside to cool.'),
('402', '7', 'Chop and rinse the romaine.'),
('402', '8', 'Cut supremes from the orange.  Get the onions out and drain them. Pat as many dry as you want for the salad (depending on yours'' and your guests'' raw onion love - me, I like a lot!)'),
('402', '9', 'Now construct your salad - put the romaine, oranges and onion in a large bowl, and toss with a generous amount of dressing.'),
('402', '10', 'Remove it to your serving bowl and serve with the toasted pecans alongside (who need croutons when you have toasted nuts?)  That''s it!'),
('408', '1', 'Heat 1/4 cup oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat until it shimmers, then cook bread crumbs, stirring constantly, until deep golden and crisp, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
('408', '2', 'Transfer bread crumbs to a bowl and toss with dill and 1/4 teaspoon each of salt and black pepper.'),
('408', '3', 'Wipe out skillet, then cook onions with 1/4 teaspoon salt in remaining 1/2 cup oil over medium heat, stirring frequently, until very soft, 12 to 15 minutes.'),
('408', '4', 'Add anchovies and cook, mashing anchovies into onions, until dissolved.'),
('408', '5', 'Meanwhile, cook bucatini in a pasta pot of boiling salted water (2 tablespoons salt for 5 quarts water) until al dente. Reserve  1/2 cup cooking water, then drain pasta.'),
('408', '6', 'Stir red-pepper flakes and reserved water into anchovy sauce, then add pasta and toss to combine.'),
('408', '7', 'Add about half of bread crumbs and toss to coat.'),
('408', '8', 'Serve sprinkled with remaining bread crumbs.'),
('411', '1', 'In a large bowl, mash the anchovies and garlic to a paste. Mash in the white wine vinegar, then slowly blend in the vegetable oil. Fold in the green and red cabbages and season with salt and pepper.'),
('411', '2', 'Serve at room temperature or lightly chilled.'),
('412', '1', 'Preheat your oven (with a stone, if you have) to 500 degrees for 2 hours.'),
('412', '2', 'Place the pizza dough on a lightly-floured counter top, and press outward into a thick disk (leaving a 1" unpressed area along the edge).  Pick up the disk and let it drape over the backs of your hands, letting gravity help you stretch it into a 12-14" disk.'),
('412', '3', 'Place the dough on a peel (or overturned cookie sheet or cutting board) that''s lightly dusted with semolina or other type of flour.'),
('412', '4', 'Scatter the mozzarella on top of the dough, then the asparagus and clumps of the goat cheese in whatever artful pattern you desire.  Side the pizza onto the preheated stone in your oven, and bake ~7-10 minutes, until the crust browns and the cheese melts.'),
('412', '5', 'Remove the pizza from the oven, and scatter the lemon zest and chili flakes on top.'),
('412', '6', 'Add anchovies, if desired.  Slice and serve.'),
('413', '1', 'Slice off the stems of the cherry peppers and discard. Scrape out the ribs and seeds. In a ceramic or glass bowl, cover the cherry peppers with the vinegar. Weight down the peppers with a plate and refrigerate overnight.'),
('413', '2', 'Drain the peppers. save the vinegar for another use. Stuff each pepper with 1 anchovy fillet and 2 capers. Pack the peppers into a glass jar.'),
('413', '3', 'Add the fennel seeds and enough olive oil to cover the peppers completely. refrigerate.'),
('413', '4', 'Serve with Pecorino cheese and toasts.'),
('414', '1', 'In a medium saucepan, combine the olive oil, fennel seeds and peppercorns and bring to a simmer over moderately low heat. Season the tuna with salt and add it to the saucepan. Simmer the tuna steak over low heat, turning once, until barely pink in the center, about 15 minutes.'),
('414', '2', 'Transfer to a plate and scrape off the fennel and peppercorns. Strain and reserve the oil.'),
('414', '3', 'Meanwhile, in a large bowl, blend the mayonnaise with the minced anchovies, capers, garlic and 1 tablespoon of the fresh lemon juice. Stir the celery, onion and olives into the dressing. Using a fork, break the tuna into 1-inch pieces, then fold into the dressing. Season with salt.'),
('414', '4', 'Set 2 avocado halves on each of 4 plates, skin side down.'),
('414', '5', 'Drizzle the avocado flesh with some of the reserved spice-infused olive oil and the remaining 1 tablespoon of fresh lemon juice. Spoon about 1/2 cup of the tuna salad into the center of each avocado half. Top the tuna salad with the pea shoots or alfalfa sprouts and serve.'),
('415', '1', 'In a blender, puree the avocado with the buttermilk, parsley, mayonnaise, sour cream, chives, tarragon, anchovy and 1 1/2 teaspoons of the Champagne vinegar. Scrape the dressing into a bowl and season with salt and pepper.'),
('415', '2', 'Add the chopped chicken breast and toss to coat.'),
('415', '3', 'In another bowl, whisk the olive oil with the remaining 2 teaspoons of Champagne vinegar. Stir in the diced cucumbers and tomato and season with salt and pepper.'),
('415', '4', 'Mound the baby arugula on plates. Pile the chicken salad on the arugula. Spoon the cucumber and tomato salad alongside and serve right away.'),
('416', '1', 'Bring a pot of salty water to boil.  Cook the pasta until al dente, reserving some pasta cooking water.'),
('416', '2', 'In the meantime, heat the olive oil in a medium skillet over medium heat.'),
('416', '3', 'Add the garlic and chili and cook until the garlic is fragrant and soft, 1-2 minutes.'),
('416', '4', 'Add the anchovy fillets and mash them into the olive oil until they melt.  Continue cooking until the garlic is quite soft and just beginning to turn golden, but not yet brown.'),
('416', '5', 'Remove the red chilies if you used them.'),
('416', '6', 'Add the pasta to the skillet and toss to coat in the sauce.'),
('416', '7', 'Add a little pasta cooking water and continue stirring to create a sauce with the olive oil.'),
('416', '8', 'Serve immediately.'),
('420', '1', '1 Toast breadcrumbs: Toast crumbs in a little olive oil in a large skillet on medium high heat until lightly browned.'),
('421', '1', 'Food'),
('421', '2', 'FoodRecipe: Kale Caesar'),
('421', '3', 'Kale salad'),
('421', '4', 'Gina Ferazzi / Los Angeles Times (Gina Ferazzi / Los Angeles Times)Kale Caesar'),
('421', '5', 'Total time: 30 minutes'),
('421', '6', 'Servings: 4 to 6Note: Adapted from "Tartine Bread" by Chad Robertson.Caesar dressing2 lemons3 cloves garlic6 olive oil-packed anchovy fillets1 egg yolk'),
('421', '7', 'Salt2 cups olive oil'),
('421', '8', 'To make the dressing, grate the zest from 1 lemon.'),
('421', '9', 'Cut both lemons in half.'),
('421', '10', 'Place the garlic, anchovies and lemon zest in a mortar and pound with a pestle to make a thick paste.'),
('421', '11', 'Add the egg yolk, a pinch of salt and a squeeze of lemon juice and stir thoroughly to combine. Continuing to stir, pour in 1/2 cup of the oil, drop by drop. The mixture should look smooth and creamy, a sign that you are building a stable emulsion. Continuing to stir, begin adding the oil in a slow stream. The dressing should thicken. Periodically stop pouring in the oil and add a squeeze of lemon. Taste the dressing and add more salt and lemon juice to taste.'),
('421', '12', 'Add water, a small spoonful at a time, stirring to thin dressing to the consistency of heavy cream. This makes about 2 cups dressing. You may not use all the dressing for the salad. the remainder will keep, covered and refrigerated, for up to 2 days.Croutons3 slices day-old bread, each 1 inch thick, torn into 1 1/2-inch chunks2 tablespoons olive oil'),
('421', '13', 'Salt1/2 teaspoon herbes de Provence (optional)To make the croutons, preheat the oven to 400 degrees. In a bowl, toss the torn bread with the olive oil and a pinch of salt. If you are using the herbs, add them too.'),
('421', '14', 'Spread the bread evenly on a baking sheet and bake until golden brown and crisp, about 15 minutes. Midway through the baking time, redistribute the croutons if they are coloring unevenly.Salad assembly2 pounds black kale, center stems removed, and torn into bite-sized pieces'),
('421', '15', 'Croutons'),
('421', '16', 'Caesar dressing2/3 cup grated or shaved aged Parmesan cheese'),
('421', '17', 'In a large bowl, combine the kale and croutons.'),
('421', '18', 'Pour dressing over the top and toss to coat (you may not use all the dressing).'),
('421', '19', 'Add the Parmesan, toss again and serve.Each of 6 servings: 522 calories. 9 grams protein. 23 grams carbohydrates. 2 grams fiber. 45 grams fat. 8 grams saturated fat. 27 mg cholesterol. 3 grams sugar. 493 mg sodium.Privacy Policy'),
('421', '20', 'Copyright 2016, Los Angeles Times'),
('421', '21', 'Cooking'),
('421', '22', 'Lifestyle and Leisure'),
('421', '23', 'Holiday gifts: A baker''s dozen of great cookbooks'),
('421', '24', 'Photos: Cookbooks worth giving (and receiving)Recipes from some of fall''s best cookbooks'),
('421', '25', 'Loading'),
('421', '26', 'Most Popular'),
('421', '27', 'Local'),
('421', '28', 'State Primary'),
('421', '29', 'Sports'),
('421', '30', 'Entertainment'),
('421', '31', 'Education'),
('421', '32', 'Opinion'),
('421', '33', 'Place An Ad72'),
('422', '1', 'While dough is rising in the pan, make the filling: Tie thyme, parsley, and bay leaf together with a piece of kitchen twine to make a bouquet garni. In a large straight-sided skillet, heat oil over medium heat.'),
('422', '2', 'Add onions, garlic, bouquet garni, and salt. Cover, and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Reduce heat to medium low, and continue to cook, covered, stirring occasionally until very soft and translucent, about 25 minutes more.'),
('422', '3', 'Transfer to a sieve to drain any excess liquid.'),
('422', '4', 'Remove and discard bouquet garni.'),
('423', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350F.'),
('423', '2', 'Place butter on heavy large rimmed baking sheet. place in oven until butter melts, about 5 minutes.'),
('423', '3', 'Spread half of onions on baking sheet. top with 3 thyme sprigs, 2 rosemary sprigs and 1 bay leaf. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('423', '4', 'Drizzle with 3 tablespoons oil. Top with remaining onions, 3 thyme sprigs, 2 rosemary sprigs, and 1 bay leaf. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('423', '5', 'Drizzle with 3 tablespoons oil (onion layer will be about 2 1/2 inches thick but will settle during baking).'),
('423', '6', 'Bake until onions are very tender and golden, stirring and turning every 30 minutes, about 2 hours total. Cool. Discard herb sprigs and bay leaves. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover. chill. Bring to room temperature before using.)'),
('424', '1', 'In a food processor, combine 4 of the anchovy fillets with the bread crumbs, garlic, parsley and  1/2 cup of the olive oil. process until evenly blended.'),
('424', '2', 'Season the chicken thighs with salt. In a large bowl, toss the chicken with the bread crumb mixture. Cover and refrigerate for 15 minutes.'),
('424', '3', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan. In a pot of boiling, salted water, blanch the snap peas until bright green, about 1 minute.'),
('424', '4', 'Drain and pat dry.'),
('424', '5', 'Grill the chicken thighs over moderate heat until they are lightly charred, crisp and cooked through, about 10 minutes per side.'),
('424', '6', 'Transfer the thighs to a platter.'),
('424', '7', 'In a large skillet, heat the remaining  3 tablespoons of olive oil.'),
('424', '8', 'Add the shallots and the remaining anchovy fillet and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until the shallots are softened, about  5 minutes.'),
('424', '9', 'Add the snap peas and cook, tossing a few times, until heated through, about 2 minutes. Season the snap peas with salt and transfer to a serving bowl.'),
('424', '10', 'Serve the chicken with the snap peas.'),
('425', '1', 'Light a grill or preheat the broiler and position a rack 8 inches from the heat. In a small bowl, combine the shallot and vinegar. Lightly rub the steak with some of the olive oil, sprinkle generously with salt and pepper and let stand for 10 minutes.'),
('425', '2', 'Grill or broil the steak, turning once, for 12 to 13 minutes for medium-rare meat.'),
('425', '3', 'Transfer the steak to a cutting board and let rest for 5 minutes, then thinly slice the meat.'),
('425', '4', 'Brush the bread on both sides with the remaining olive oil and grill or broil until golden on both sides. Rub one side of each toast with the garlic and set 4 of the slices, garlic side up, on a work surface. Arrange the tomatoes on the toast and season with salt and pepper. Spoon the shallot vinegar over the tomatoes, and top with the arugula, steak and anchovies. Cover with the remaining toast and cut in half.'),
('425', '5', 'Serve immediately.'),
('426', '1', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan. In a large saucepan of boiling salted water, cook the fusilli, stirring occasionally, until al dente.'),
('426', '2', 'Drain and transfer to a large bowl.'),
('426', '3', 'Meanwhile, brush the cut sides of the zucchini with 1 tablespoon of the lemon juice and season with salt and pepper. Grill the zucchini, cut side down, over a medium-hot fire until lightly charred, about 3 minutes. Turn the zucchini and move them to the sides of the grill.'),
('426', '4', 'Brush the chicken breasts with 2 teaspoons of the olive oil and season them with salt and pepper. Set the chicken breasts in the center of the grill and grill until cooked through, turning once, about 10 minutes.'),
('426', '5', 'Transfer the chicken and zucchini to a platter and let stand for 5 minutes.'),
('426', '6', 'In a small bowl, combine the very finely chopped anchovies, minced garlic and the remaining 2 tablespoons each of lemon juice and olive oil. season with salt and pepper.'),
('426', '7', 'Cut the chicken and zucchini into bite-size pieces and add them to the fusilli.'),
('426', '8', 'Add the red pepper and the anchovy dressing and toss well. Sprinkle the basil on top, season with salt and pepper, toss again and serve.'),
('427', '1', 'In a medium bowl, using the back of a fork, mash the anchovies with the roasted garlic paste, cumin and extra-virgin olive oil. Stir in the sour cream and lime juice. Fold in the smoked salmon, jalapeo, red onion, capers and chopped cilantro and season with salt and pepper.'),
('427', '2', 'Arrange the tortilla chips on a platter. Spoon a heaping teaspoon of the smoked salmon tartare onto each chip, top with a cilantro leaf and serve.'),
('428', '1', 'Heat 3 tablespoons of the oil in a large enameled cast-iron casserole. Lightly flour the fish and season with salt and pepper. Cook over moderate heat until lightly browned and cooked through, about 3 minutes per side, depending on the thickness of the fish.'),
('428', '2', 'Transfer the fish to a platter.'),
('428', '3', 'Add the garlic to the oil and cook over moderate heat until deep golden, about 2 minutes. discard the garlic.'),
('428', '4', 'Add the escarole to the casserole along with the anchovies, olives and capers. Cook, stirring constantly, until the escarole turns bright green and wilts, about 3 minutes.'),
('428', '5', 'Transfer the escarole to a bowl.'),
('428', '6', 'Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil in the casserole.'),
('428', '7', 'Add the tomatoes and cook over moderately high heat, stirring, until thickened, about 5 minutes.'),
('428', '8', 'Add the tomato sauce to the escarole and season with salt and pepper.'),
('428', '9', 'Garnish with parsley and serve with the fish.'),
('430', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('430', '2', 'Put the beans in a steamer basket and steam over 1 inch of boiling water until crisp-tender, 4 minutes. transfer to a large roasting pan.'),
('430', '3', 'Lightly squeeze the tomatoes and add to the pan.'),
('430', '4', 'Add the olives, bell pepper, anchovies and basil, toss with 1/4 cup of the olive oil and season with salt and pepper.'),
('430', '5', 'Brush the tuna steaks with 1 tablespoon of the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Set the tuna on the vegetables. Nestle 4 ramekins among the vegetables and crack an egg into each ramekin.'),
('430', '6', 'Drizzle the eggs with 1 tablespoon of the oil and season with salt and pepper'),
('430', '7', 'Roast the tuna, vegetables and eggs in the center of the oven for 15 minutes, until the fish is slightly rare in the center and the egg whites are set, but the yolks are still runny.'),
('430', '8', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, whisk the remaining 1/4 cup of oil with the lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.'),
('430', '9', 'Drizzle the dressing over the vegetables and tuna steaks.'),
('430', '10', 'Transfer to plates and serve immediately.'),
('431', '1', 'In a small bowl, combine the water with the yeast and let stand until foamy, about 5 minutes.'),
('431', '2', 'In a large bowl, stir the flour with the salt. Make a well in the center and pour in the yeast mixture. Stir gently until a rough dough forms. Turn out onto a lightly floured work surface and knead gently until smooth.'),
('431', '3', 'Transfer to an oiled bowl and cover with plastic wrap.'),
('431', '4', 'Let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.'),
('431', '5', 'Cook the escarole in a large pot of boiling salted water for 4 minutes. drain and rinse under cold water. Squeeze the escarole dry, then chop coarsely.'),
('431', '6', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('431', '7', 'Toast the pine nuts in a pie pan for 4 minutes.'),
('431', '8', 'In a large skillet, heat the extra-virgin olive oil.'),
('431', '9', 'Add the garlic and cook over low heat for 1 minute.'),
('431', '10', 'Add the escarole, toasted pine nuts, olives and anchovies and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, then spread the filling on a large plate to cool.'),
('431', '11', 'Lightly oil a 12-inch-round pizza or tart pan. Punch down the dough and cut it in half. On a lightly floured surface, roll out 1 piece of the dough 1/4 inch thick. Trim it into a 12-inch round. let rise for 10 minutes.'),
('431', '12', 'Roll the other dough half into a 13-inch round 1/4 inch thick.'),
('431', '13', 'Transfer the larger round to the pizza pan, draping it evenly over the sides.'),
('431', '14', 'Spread the escarole filling evenly over the dough in the pan. Fold the remaining round in half and set it on the escarole filling, unfolding it to cover the top. Crimp the edges of the pie to seal. Using a fork, prick the top of the pizza all over.'),
('431', '15', 'Brush with pure olive oil and bake in the center of the oven for about 45 minutes, or until golden brown.'),
('431', '16', 'Transfer the pizza to a rack to cool for 10 minutes.'),
('431', '17', 'Cut into wedges and serve warm or at room temperature.'),
('432', '1', 'In separate small bowls, cover the olives, anchovies and raisins with hot water and let soak for 10 minutes.'),
('432', '2', 'Drain well. Coarsely chop the olives and finely chop the anchovies. In a small bowl, combine the olives, anchovies and raisins with the parsley, scallions, garlic and the 2 tablespoons of grated pecorino cheese.'),
('432', '3', 'Coat a 10- or 12-inch cazuela or ovenproof skillet with 2 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('432', '4', 'Spread half of the broccoli rabe in the cazuela in an even layer. Sprinkle with the olive mixture and cover with the remaining broccoli rabe. Press a piece of parchment paper on top of the broccoli rabe and cover the cazuela tightly. Cook over low heat until the broccoli rabe is tender, about 40 minutes.'),
('432', '5', 'Add the wine, cover and cook for 10 minutes longer.'),
('432', '6', 'Transfer the cazuela to a padded or wooden surface. (To avoid thermal shock, do not place it on a cold stone or metal surface.) Uncover, season with salt and pepper and let stand.'),
('432', '7', 'Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 40'),
('432', '8', 'Bring a large saucepan of salted water to a boil.'),
('432', '9', 'Add the pasta and cook until al dente.'),
('432', '10', 'Drain the pasta and return it to the saucepan. Toss with the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Gently fold the pasta into the broccoli rabe. Sprinkle with pecorino and bake until bubbling, about 10 minutes.'),
('432', '11', 'Serve hot or warm.'),
('433', '1', 'In a mini food processor, pulse the anchovy fillets with the smashed garlic and the lemon juice until finely minced.'),
('433', '2', 'Add the olive oil and process the anchovy mixture until smooth.'),
('433', '3', 'Add the chopped olives, thyme and rosemary and pulse to blend. Season the Provenal dressing lightly with salt and pepper and reserve.'),
('433', '4', 'Light a grill or preheat a cast-iron grill pan. Season the lamb chops generously with salt and pepper. Grill the lamb chops over high heat, turning them once, until browned all over, about 7 minutes for medium-rare meat.'),
('433', '5', 'Transfer the lamb chops to a large serving platter, spoon the Provenal dressing on top and serve.'),
('434', '1', 'In a large skillet, heat the olive oil. In a small bowl, toss the capers with the cornstarch and transfer to a sieve. shake off the excess cornstarch.'),
('434', '2', 'Add the coated capers to the oil and fry over high heat, tilting and gently shaking the pan, until the capers are crispy and golden, about 3 minutes.'),
('434', '3', 'Drain the capers, reserving 2 tablespoons of the oil in the skillet.'),
('434', '4', 'Spread the capers on a paper towellined plate.'),
('434', '5', 'Add the anchovies and garlic to the skillet and cook over high heat, stirring, until the garlic is golden and the anchovies dissolve, about 3 minutes.'),
('434', '6', 'Add the prosciutto, separating the ribbons, and cook until lightly browned, about 1 minute.'),
('434', '7', 'Add the tomatoes and crushed red pepper and cook just until the tomatoes begin to break down, about 3 minutes. Stir in the basil.'),
('434', '8', 'Meanwhile, in a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the pasta until al dente.'),
('434', '9', 'Drain, reserving 1/2 cup of the cooking water. Return the pasta to the pot along with the water and pour the sauce on top. Toss over high heat just until the sauce is thickened, about 2 minutes.'),
('434', '10', 'Serve the pasta in bowls, garnished with the crispy capers. Pass the grated cheese at the table.'),
('435', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('435', '2', 'Put the eggplant and bell pepper on a baking sheet. Roast the bell pepper, turning it occasionally, for about 40 minutes, or until blistered all over, and the eggplant for about 1 hour, or until it has collapsed.'),
('435', '3', 'Transfer the vegetables to a plate.'),
('435', '4', 'On a large baking sheet, lightly brush both sides of the baguette slices with olive oil.'),
('435', '5', 'Bake in the oven for about 10 minutes, or until golden brown.'),
('435', '6', 'When the vegetables are cool enough to handle, remove the skins, seeds and stems.'),
('435', '7', 'Transfer the eggplant to a colander and let drain for 30 minutes. Finely chop the eggplant and transfer to a bowl.'),
('435', '8', 'Cut the bell pepper into 1/4-inch dice and add to the eggplant. Stir in the 1 1/2 tablespoons of olive oil and season with salt and black pepper.'),
('435', '9', 'Cut 1 of the tomatoes in half crosswise. Rub 16 of the baguette toasts with the cut sides of the halved tomato. Top each toast with a piece of ham, folding it to fit neatly. Sprinkle with some of the chives.'),
('435', '10', 'Cut the other tomato crosswise into 8 slices, then cut each slice in half.'),
('435', '11', 'Spread the eggplant mixture on the remaining 16 baguette toasts and top each with a half slice of tomato and half an anchovy.'),
('435', '12', 'Serve the canaps at room temperature.'),
('436', '1', 'Put the celery in a large bowl of ice water and refrigerate until curled and very crisp, at least 2 hours.'),
('436', '2', 'In a bowl, whisk the olive oil with the lemon juice, anchovies, garlic and lemon zest. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('436', '3', 'Drain the celery and pat dry. Return the celery to the dry bowl and toss with the olives and dressing.'),
('436', '4', 'Transfer the antipasto to a platter, scatter the ricotta salata over the top and serve.'),
('437', '1', 'In a food processor, blend the scallions with the garlic, ginger, anchovies and crushed red pepper.'),
('437', '2', 'Add the brown sugar, soy sauce, oil, black pepper and salt. blend.'),
('437', '3', 'Add the pineapple juice.'),
('437', '4', 'Make small slashes on the meaty parts of the chicken wings.'),
('437', '5', 'Spread the wings in 2 very large roasting pans and pour the marinade on top. Rub the marinade into the wings. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bring to room temperature before roasting.'),
('437', '6', 'Preheat the oven to 50'),
('437', '7', 'Arrange the wings in a single layer on large, oiled, rimmed baking sheets. pour any remaining marinade on top. Roast the wings on as many shelves as possible, rotating the pans, for 1 hour, or until the wings are deeply browned and crisp.'),
('437', '8', 'Serve piping hot.'),
('438', '1', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('438', '2', 'Arrange broccoli florets on a Silpat or parchment-lined cookie sheet. Season with salt and pepper and drizzle with olive oil. Roast for 20-25 minutes and remove.'),
('438', '3', 'In a small skillet, melt butter and olive oil over medium heat.'),
('438', '4', 'Add garlic and anchovy and saute for about three minutes.'),
('438', '5', 'Add wine and lemon and allow to reduce for a minute or two. Season with black pepper if desired.'),
('438', '6', 'Meantime, in another small skillet over medium heat, toast almonds until they are lightly browned, taking care not to burn them.'),
('438', '7', 'Drizzle sauce and sprinkle almonds and parmesan cheese over broccoli, then serve. Or, dip the broccoli in the sauce at the table. Enjoy!'),
('439', '1', 'Preheat oven to 37'),
('439', '2', 'Oil a 9 x 9 baking dish (or two, if your red peppers are large) and put the peppers in the baking dish.'),
('439', '3', 'Melt the onions in the olive oil over medium low heat until soft.'),
('439', '4', 'Add the garlic and cook for a few more minutes.  The garlic should not color.'),
('439', '5', 'Mix the onion and garlic mixture into the cooked white rice.'),
('439', '6', 'Add all other ingredients and mix well.'),
('439', '7', 'Add pepper to taste.'),
('439', '8', 'Loosely fill red peppers with rice mixture.'),
('439', '9', 'Bake for 25 minutes.  If the mixture seems dry, dribble more olive oil on during baking.'),
('439', '10', 'Serve warm or cold.'),
('440', '1', 'Remove most of the stems from rabe.'),
('440', '2', 'Cut greens into 2 or 3 inch pieces. Boil and salt water. Blanche the greens for five minutes or so.'),
('440', '3', 'Drain and set aside.'),
('440', '4', 'Heat three tablespoons of olive oil over medium heat.'),
('440', '5', 'Add chopped garlic and anchovies, along with a good pinch of pepperonchino.'),
('440', '6', 'Saute three minutes or so, until anchovies are dissolved.'),
('440', '7', 'Add rabe, stir and saute about 5 minutes so it soaks up the oil.'),
('440', '8', 'Add a bit of salt.'),
('440', '9', 'Add chicken broth and vinegar and saute, stirring as needed, till the rabe is tender but by no means mushy. There should be a bit of tasty liquid but not too much.'),
('440', '10', 'Boil orecchiete in salted water, watching like a hawk that it doesn''t overcook. I recently bought very good orecchiette that was ready three minutes before the recommended cooking time.'),
('440', '11', 'Drain pasta when done.'),
('440', '12', 'Combine pasta and rabe over medium heat for a minute or two. Check for salt. A bit of oil will not hurt.'),
('440', '13', 'Serve with generous grating of parmeggiano, a drizzle of oil, black pepper and a little fine sea salt.'),
('441', '1', 'In a large stockpot, bring salted water to a boil. Cook the pasta al dente.'),
('441', '2', 'While the pasta cooks, heat some olive oil in a large wide saute pan with sides. I use an AllClad 4 qt. saucier.'),
('441', '3', 'Add the mushrooms and season with the red pepper flakes and salt and pepper. Cook slowly, undisturbed, until the mushrooms have given off their liquid and reabsorbed it - about 10 minutes.'),
('441', '4', 'Add the garlic and stir and cook briefly. Push the mushrooms off to the side, add the butter and anchovies to the center of the pan and cook and mash the fish up into the butter. Now stir the mushrooms back in.'),
('441', '5', 'Hopefully, the pasta is now ready, so drain it into a colander, and add it into the pan with the mushrooms and anchovies. Stir it around, then add all the spinach and toss to cook. The heat of the pasta will wilt/cook the spinach.'),
('441', '6', 'I like to serve this in a large shallow serving bowl.'),
('441', '7', 'Drizzle a couple of tablespoons of olive oil into the bowl.'),
('441', '8', 'Stir the pasta, spinach, mushroom mix up well and add pasta water as necessary to make it a little saucy.'),
('441', '9', 'Place in the serving bowl. Top with pine nuts, breadcrumbs, parmesian and lemon zest.'),
('442', '1', 'Mix together the flour, salt and sugar in a food processor.'),
('442', '2', 'Dice the butter into 1/2 inch cubes.'),
('442', '3', 'Add to the processor and pulce 5 times (1 1/2 seconds each pulse) until the mixture has pea-sized globules of butter still visible in the flour.'),
('442', '4', 'Add the cold water while quickly pulsing the flour mixture to evenly distribute the water through the butter-flour mix (do not overmix).'),
('442', '5', 'Dump out the mixture onto plastic wrap.  Bring together into a ball inside the plastic wrap and then flatten into a disc.'),
('442', '6', 'Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes and up to 24 hours.'),
('442', '7', 'Roll out or freeze dough for up to 1 month.'),
('442', '8', 'Preheat the oven to 425 degrees.'),
('442', '9', 'Cut the top of the head of garlic.  Wrap the garlic in foil and roast for about 45 minutes until the garlic cloves are soft.  Mash the softened garlic together with anchovy into a paste and set aside.'),
('442', '10', 'Heat olive oil in saute pan.  Slice onion and place in the pan.'),
('442', '11', 'Saute for 20-25 minutes until onion is browned and carmelized.  Season with salt and pepper.'),
('442', '12', 'Roll out the pie dough into an 11 inch round.'),
('442', '13', 'Place on parchment paper on a baking tray.'),
('442', '14', 'Smear the garlic/anchovy paste onto the bottom of the pie dough, leaving a 2 inch border.  Load the onions, goat cheese and parmesan cheese into the middle and sprinkle the top with walnuts.'),
('442', '15', 'Fold the outside 2 inch edge of the pastry over the center in an overlapping fashion (think rustic tart).'),
('442', '16', 'Brush the folded edge with egg white and sprinkle with Herbs de Provence.'),
('442', '17', 'Bake the tart at 425 F degrees for 10 minutes, then turn down to 375 degrees F and bake for another 20-25 minutes until the crust is golden.'),
('442', '18', 'Serve warm.'),
('443', '1', 'Preheat oven to 425 F. Line a 9-inch pie plate or a 9-inch fluted tart tin with a removable bottom with the piecrust.'),
('443', '2', 'Spread the onions and olives over the dough. Top with the anchovies, if desired, and sprinkle with the Parmesan.'),
('443', '3', 'Bake until the crust is golden brown and crisp, 25 to 28 minutes.'),
('444', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 50'),
('444', '2', 'In a 9-by-13-inch baking dish, toss the sliced fennel with 2 tablespoons of the oil, the anchovies and fennel seeds. Season with salt and pepper and spread the fennel in an even layer. Roast for about 15 minutes, stirring after 10, or until the fennel is tender and just beginning to brown.'),
('444', '3', 'In a small bowl, toss the bread cubes with the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil and season with salt and pepper. Set the halibut on the fennel and season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle the bread cubes over the fish and roast for about 8 minutes longer, or until the fish is cooked through and the croutons are golden and crisp. Sprinkle with the chopped fennel tops and serve.'),
('449', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.'),
('449', '2', 'Combine all the ingredients except for the parsley in a medium mixing bowl and toss to combine.'),
('449', '3', 'Spread the tomato mixture in an even layer in a 12-inch cast iron skillet or a 9 x 13 baking dish.'),
('449', '4', 'Bake for 30 minutes, until the tomatoes are caramelized and their juices have mingled nicely with the briny olives and capers.To serve, add the fresh parsley and a heap of cooked spaghetti to the pan and toss to combine.'),
('449', '5', 'Drizzle with olive oil and mangia! Alternatively, you can store the sauce for later or use it as a topping for fish or shrimp.'),
('453', '1', 'Heat olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('453', '2', 'Add onion, and saut 10 minutes. Stir in salt and anchovies. saut 10 minutes. Stir in vinegar and chopped thyme. Reduce the heat to medium-low. cook 3 minutes or until liquid is absorbed, stirring frequently. Stir in olives. Cool to room temperature.'),
('453', '3', 'Preheat oven to 37'),
('453', '4', 'Trim crusts from bread. reserve crusts for another use. Lightly coat both sides of bread with cooking spray.'),
('453', '5', 'Place 1 slice into each of 24 miniature muffin cups, pressing bread into pan to form cups (bread tips will stick up).'),
('453', '6', 'Bake at 375 for 10 minutes or until dry and golden. Carefully remove the bread cups from pan. cool on a wire rack. Spoon 1 heaping tablespoon onion mixture into each bread cup. Sprinkle evenly with whole thyme leaves.'),
('454', '1', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('454', '2', 'Add 2 tablespoons oil to pan.'),
('454', '3', 'Add garlic. cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly.'),
('454', '4', 'Add anchovies. mash in pan to form a paste. Stir in tomatoes and next 4 ingredients (through pepper). cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('454', '5', 'Bring 6 quarts water to a boil.'),
('454', '6', 'Add pasta. cook 8 minutes or until almost al dente.'),
('454', '7', 'Drain in a colander over a bowl, reserving 1/2 cup pasta water.'),
('454', '8', 'Add pasta and reserved pasta water to tomato mixture. increase heat to medium-high. Cook 5 minutes or until pasta is al dente, tossing to combine. Spoon 1 1/2 cups pasta into each of 4 bowls.'),
('454', '9', 'Drizzle each serving with 3/4 teaspoon oil. sprinkle with cheese.'),
('455', '1', 'Heat oven to 450 with a rack set 5 in. from the heat source.'),
('455', '2', 'Heat oil in a large ovenproof frying pan over high heat.'),
('455', '3', 'Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Brown chicken in hot oil on one side, about 4 minutes. Turn chicken over and add chile flakes, garlic, tomatoes, oregano, and olives.'),
('455', '4', 'Transfer pan to oven and cook until chicken is cooked through, about 20 minutes. Lay cheese over chicken and bake just until melted and browned, 2 minutes.'),
('458', '1', 'Toast pine nuts in a wide (not nonstick) frying pan over medium heat until lightly toasted, about 3 minutes.'),
('458', '2', 'Pour into a medium bowl and set aside.'),
('458', '3', 'In the same pan, heat 1 tbsp. olive oil over medium heat until just warm and add panko. Toast panko, stirring occasionally, until a shade darker, about 5 minutes.'),
('458', '4', 'Add anchovies and garlic. stir to combine well.'),
('458', '5', 'Add panko mixture to pine nuts. Stir in 1/4 tsp. salt, the lemon zest, and parsley.'),
('458', '6', 'Preheat a gas or charcoal grill to high (you can hold your hand 1 to 2 in. above cooking grate only 2 to 3 seconds).'),
('458', '7', 'Cut each radicchio head in half, cut each half into 3 wedges, and brush cut sides with olive oil. Skewer wedges onto metal skewers, 3 per skewer. Grill radicchio skewers (close lid on gas grill), 2 minutes.'),
('458', '8', 'Turn radicchio skewers over.'),
('458', '9', 'Brush fish on both sides with olive oil and grill, skin side down, 3 to 4 minutes (close lid on gas grill), or until they look opaque (cut to test) and loosen easily. Using 2 spatulas, gently turn fish over (close lid on gas grill) and cook 1 minute more.'),
('458', '10', 'Transfer fillets to plates and radicchio to a cutting board. Season fish with salt, pepper, and a few drops of lemon juice to taste.'),
('458', '11', 'Remove skewers from grilled radicchio and chop radicchio roughly. Toss with remaining lemon juice and remaining 1/2 tsp. salt. Stir remaining 3 tbsp. olive oil into bread crumbs and spoon over flesh side of fish.'),
('458', '12', 'Serve fish with radicchio.'),
('459', '1', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('459', '2', 'Add 2 tablespoons oil to pan.'),
('459', '3', 'Add garlic. cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly.'),
('459', '4', 'Add anchovies. mash in pan to form a paste. Stir in tomatoes and next 4 ingredients (through pepper). cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('459', '5', 'Bring 6 quarts water to a boil.'),
('459', '6', 'Add pasta. cook 8 minutes or until almost al dente.'),
('459', '7', 'Drain in a colander over a bowl, reserving 1/2 cup pasta water.'),
('459', '8', 'Add pasta and reserved pasta water to tomato mixture. increase heat to medium-high. Cook 5 minutes or until pasta is al dente, tossing to combine. Spoon 1 1/2 cups pasta into each of 4 bowls.'),
('459', '9', 'Drizzle each serving with 3/4 teaspoon oil. sprinkle with cheese.'),
('460', '1', 'Heat olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('460', '2', 'Add onion and anchovies to pan. Cover and cook for 25 minutes or until onion is very tender, stirring occasionally. Uncover and cook 10 minutes or until onion is golden brown, stirring often. Stir in 2 teaspoons thyme and pepper. Keep warm.'),
('460', '3', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('460', '4', 'Press dough into a 15 x 10-inch jelly-roll pan coated with cooking spray.'),
('460', '5', 'Bake at 400 for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.'),
('460', '6', 'Remove from oven. Arrange onion mixture evenly over crust. top with olives.'),
('460', '7', 'Cut into squares.'),
('460', '8', 'Garnish with thyme sprigs, if desired.'),
('460', '9', 'Serve immediately.'),
('461', '1', 'Heat oil in a small saucepan over medium heat. Stir in garlic.'),
('461', '2', 'Remove pan from heat. let stand 5 minutes.'),
('461', '3', 'Remove garlic from oil with a slotted spoon. discard garlic.'),
('461', '4', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('461', '5', 'Place bread on a baking sheet.'),
('461', '6', 'Drizzle bread with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil. toss to coat. Arrange bread in an even layer. Broil 6 inches from heat for 2 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring after 1 minute. Turn oven off.'),
('461', '7', 'Place pan on middle oven rack. close oven door.'),
('461', '8', 'Add juice and next 6 ingredients (through egg yolk) to remaining oil in pan. Cook over medium heat 30 seconds or until mixture thickens and begins to bubble around edges, stirring constantly.'),
('461', '9', 'Pour mixture into a small bowl. cool to room temperature.'),
('461', '10', 'Place lettuce in a large bowl.'),
('461', '11', 'Add egg mixture, cheese, and pepper. toss gently to coat.'),
('461', '12', 'Add bread. toss gently to combine.'),
('461', '13', 'Serve immediately.'),
('462', '1', 'Cook beans in boiling water 3 minutes. remove with a slotted spoon. Rinse under cold water. drain.'),
('462', '2', 'Place beans in a large bowl. Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.'),
('462', '3', 'Drain and rinse under cold water. drain.'),
('462', '4', 'Add pasta to beans.'),
('462', '5', 'Drain tuna through a sieve over a bowl, reserving oil. Flake tuna with a fork.'),
('462', '6', 'Add tuna and next 4 ingredients (through capers) to bowl. toss.'),
('462', '7', 'Combine reserved oil, olive oil, and remaining ingredients in a blender. process until smooth.'),
('462', '8', 'Pour oil mixture over pasta mixture. toss to coat.'),
('463', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('463', '2', 'Arrange baguette slices in an even layer on a baking sheet. Broil 1 minute or until toasted. Cool completely on baking sheet.'),
('463', '3', 'Prepare grill or grill pan.'),
('463', '4', 'Slice zucchini lengthwise into 3 equal pieces. Arrange zucchini pieces and bell pepper quarters, skin side down, in a single layer on grill rack or grill pan coated with cooking spray, and grill 3 minutes on each side or until lightly browned and crisp-tender. Chop zucchini and bell pepper. cover and keep warm.'),
('463', '5', 'Combine juice, salt, garlic, and anchovies in a small food processor. process 30 seconds or until mixture forms a paste.'),
('463', '6', 'Add oil. pulse 10 times or until combined. Spoon mixture into a small saucepan. bring to a simmer over medium-high heat.'),
('463', '7', 'Remove from heat. stir in parsley.'),
('463', '8', 'Place 2 baguette slices on each of 12 plates.'),
('463', '9', 'Drizzle each slice with about 1/2 teaspoon oil mixture, and top with about 1 tablespoon vegetables.'),
('463', '10', 'Serve immediately.'),
('464', '1', 'Osso bucco'),
('464', '2', 'Veal shanks have a richness unlike any other cut of meat and turn this stewinto an extraordinary meal.four 112in (4cm) thick veal shankssalt and freshly ground black pepper14 cup all-purpose flour2 tbsp butter2 tbsp olive oil1 small onion, chopped4 garlic cloves, chopped12 cup beef stock or water, as needed14 cup tomato paste3 tbsp chopped parsley2 anchovy fillets in oil, mincedgrated zest of 1 lemon'),
('464', '3', 'Season the veal with salt and pepper. Dredge in the flour and shake off any excess.Melt the butter with the oil in the casserole over medium-high heat.'),
('464', '4', 'Add the veal and cook,turning occasionally, about 5 minutes, or until browned all over.'),
('464', '5', 'Transfer to a plate.'),
('464', '6', 'Add the onionand garlic to the casserole and reduce the heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5minutes or until softened but not colored.Stir in the stock and tomato paste, season with salt and pepper, and bring to a boil. Return theveal to the casserole. Reduce the heat to low and cover. Simmer for 112 hours or until the veal istender. Check the stew occasionally, and if the cooking liquid has reduced too much, add morestock. The finished cooking liquid should be thick.Stir the parsley, anchovies, and lemon zest into the casserole. Adjust the seasoning as requiredand serve immediately.Good wIth a saffron-flavored risotto or cooked long-grain rice or your favorite pasta.The stew can be cooked, then chilled for up to 2 days. Reheat gently .'),
('467', '1', 'Heat the oven to 180c.Weigh out all the ingredients.'),
('467', '2', 'Remove any large stalks from the watercress and mint.Either finely chop all of ingredients (except for the salmon) and mix them together in a bowl with the olive oil or blend them in a food processor with the olive oil.'),
('467', '3', 'Remove any bones from the salmon fillets and put them, skin side down, onto an oiled baking tray. Then coat the top side of each filet with the salsa verde.'),
('467', '4', 'Put the tray into oven for 15 minutes. Then remove the salmon from the oven and allow them to rest for 5 minutes.'),
('467', '5', 'Serve. We served it with pan roasted potatoes.'),
('468', '1', 'My good friend Hank who lives in a converted church in Lincoln, R.I. reacted to a piece I wrote about Skinny Bitch''s vegetarian advocacy with a strongly worded email:hmm, let''s see-give me a pack of Camels....a 5th of bourbon and for lunch I''ll have tuna and steak tartar....with bacon. Clearly what''s good for the goose is not good for my friend Hank. And I have to agree with him--except for the "pack of Camels"--all the rest sounds good.So for Hank and all other guys, here''s my version of a dream meal: Caesar Salad,'),
('468', '2', 'Sauteed Shrimp with Shiitake Mushrooms, Grilled Steak with a'),
('468', '3', 'Baked Tomato, and a Dirty Martini.'),
('468', '4', 'Baked Tomato'),
('468', '5', 'Get the tomatoes started while you prepare the rest of the meal, so they''ll be ready to serve when you''ve finished the other dishes.'),
('469', '1', 'Remove the heads from the shrimp as well as the legs and shells, but leave the tails on. Set the shells aside for the stock, then devein the shrimp by making a shallow incision along the back side of the shrimp from head to tail and removing any brown "gunk".'),
('469', '2', 'Remove the legs and claws from the crab by twisting and pulling, this will subdue the poor guy pretty quickly.'),
('469', '3', 'Remove the little flap on the underside of the crab then pry the top shell away from the body, reserving for the stock. Use a wrench or nutcracker to crack the legs and claws.'),
('469', '4', 'Cut each body into 4 segments. Refrigerate until ready to use.'),
('469', '5', 'Heat a large stockpot over medium heat until hot.'),
('469', '6', 'Add about 2 tablespoons of olive oil then add the onions, celery, parsnips, and garlic. Fry until soft, fragrant and starting to brown around the edges.'),
('469', '7', 'Add the wine and turn up to heat to bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes to burn off the alcohol.'),
('469', '8', 'Add the water, fish bones, shrimp heads/shells, the top shells of the crab, thyme, oregano, parsley, bay leaves, and salt. Bring this to a boil and skim off any foam that accumulates on the surface.Once there is no more foam forming, turn the heat down to medium low, cover and simmer for 2 hours.Strain through a colander and press on the solids with a potato masher to get every last bit of stock out. Discard the solids.Rinse the pot, place over medium heat and add a splash of oil. Fry the onions and garlic until soft and fragrant, then add the tomatoes and basil.Return the fish stock you made to the pot along with the crushed stewed tomatoes, and anchovy, and bring to a boil.Lower the heat to medium low then add the crab, snapper, and clams and cover the pot.'),
('469', '9', 'Let this simmer until the clams are open and the fish is cooked (about 10 minutes).'),
('469', '10', 'Add the shrimp and continue cooking until the shrimp just turn pink (another minute or two).'),
('469', '11', 'Serve the Cioppino in large bowls with some chopped parsley or chervil to garnish, and a big hunk of crusty sourdough bread.'),
('471', '1', 'In a medium bowl, toss the carrots with the vinegar and sugar.'),
('471', '2', 'Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. stir occasionally.'),
('471', '3', 'In a food processor, combine the basil, anchovies, lime juice, fish sauce, crushed red pepper and chopped garlic and process to a paste. With the machine on, slowly pour in the olive oil and puree until blended. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('471', '4', 'Let stand at room temperature for at least 30 minutes.'),
('471', '5', 'Preheat the broiler.'),
('471', '6', 'Spread the cut sides of the baguettes with the butter. Toast 3 inches from the heat. Rub the toasted sides with the garlic clove. spread with the mayonnaise.'),
('471', '7', 'Drizzle with the Sriracha. Arrange the cucumber, carrots and piquillo peppers on the bottoms and garnish with the cilantro.'),
('471', '8', 'Spread the tops with the pesto and close the sandwiches.'),
('471', '9', 'Cut in half and serve.'),
('472', '1', 'In a mini food processor or blender, puree the anchovies with the garlic. With the machine on, pour in the olive oil until blended.'),
('472', '2', 'Transfer the anchoade to a serving bowl. serve with the vegetables.'),
('473', '1', 'In a food processor, combine the shallots, garlic, anchovies, sun-dried tomatoes, tomato paste, bay leaves and marmalade and process to a smooth paste.'),
('473', '2', 'Transfer to a large bowl and add the wine, orange juice, vinegar, rosemary, orange zest, salt, crushed red pepper and black pepper.'),
('473', '3', 'Add the ribs and toss to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate, turning occasionally for at least 6 hours or overnight.'),
('473', '4', 'Preheat the oven to 37'),
('473', '5', 'Remove the ribs from the marinade and arrange them in a single layer on 2 large rimmed baking sheets. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour.'),
('473', '6', 'Pour the marinade into a medium saucepan and bring to a boil. let cool.'),
('473', '7', 'Drain any fat and liquid from the ribs. Continue baking, uncovered, for about 1 hour longer, turning and basting occasionally with the reserved marinade, until the meat is very tender.'),
('473', '8', 'Transfer the ribs to a platter and serve right away.'),
('474', '1', 'Heat oil in a large pot over medium heat.'),
('474', '2', 'Add garlic, rosemary, and anchovies, and saut 1 minute.'),
('474', '3', 'Add tomato and next 4 ingredients, and bring to a boil. reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes.'),
('474', '4', 'Add pasta. simmer 11 minutes or until pasta is al dente (softened but still firm). Stir in kale and parsley, and cook 5 minutes. To serve, top with Parmesan cheese.'),
('474', '5', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('474', '6', 'Note: The soup thickens as it stands. To reheat, thin with water or additional chicken broth.'),
('475', '1', 'Remove the thick stem from the center of the kale by carefully tearing away the bottom part of the leaves and then pulling up along the stem. The leaf should come away in tact, missing the center when the stem once was.Stack the kale leaves with the largest at the bottom, smallest at the top.'),
('475', '2', 'Roll the leaves width-wise into a cigar. Turn the roll over so that the opening is touching the cutting board. Thinly slice the cigar  the result will be beautiful ribbons of kale.In a large mixing bowl, toss the kale ribbons together with the dressing. Taste for seasoning and serve with nuts sprinkled on top, if using.In a small food processor or blender, combine the anchovies and oil from the tin, capers, garlic, and lemon zest and juice. Pulse until coarsely chopped.Meanwhile, melt the butter in a small saucepan or in the microwave.'),
('475', '3', 'Add the olive oil to the processor and puree until emulsified. Stream in the hot melted butter and pulse a few more times until combined. Taste for seasoning - the anchovies and capers can be salty, so you dont want to add more until the end.To serve, toss vinaigrette with raw kale, escarole, or spinach. Or serve alongside raw vegetables as a more traditional dipping sauce. Dressing can keep for up to a week in the fridge. Reheat slightly in the microwave before using.'),
('478', '1', 'Heat the Bertolli spread in a saucepan and saut garlic and anchovies until soft.'),
('478', '2', 'Add capers, olives and tomatoes and simmer for 15-20 minutes.Meanwhile cook the dried spaghetti according to pack instructions.'),
('478', '3', 'Drain.'),
('478', '4', 'Add the Italian spaghetti to the sauce, toss well together and serve sprinkled with parsley.'),
('478', '5', 'Heat the Bertolli spread in a saucepan and saut garlic and anchovies until soft.'),
('478', '6', 'Add capers, olives and tomatoes and simmer for 15-20 minutes.Meanwhile cook the dried spaghetti according to pack instructions.'),
('478', '7', 'Drain.'),
('478', '8', 'Add the Italian spaghetti to the sauce, toss well together and serve sprinkled with parsley.'),
('479', '1', 'Place first 7 ingredients in a blender or food processor. process until smooth.'),
('479', '2', 'Add parsley and remaining ingredients. process until herbs are minced.'),
('480', '1', 'Combine all ingredients in a food processor. pulse 10 times or until olives are finely chopped.'),
('481', '1', 'Place egg in a small bowl or coffee mug. cover with boiling water.'),
('481', '2', 'Let stand 1 minute. Rinse egg with cold water. break egg into a small bowl.'),
('481', '3', 'Combine pepper and next 3 ingredients (through garlic) in a mini food processor. process until minced.'),
('481', '4', 'Add egg and juice. process 1 minute or until thick. Gradually add oil and 1 tablespoon water, processing until blended.'),
('481', '5', 'Combine croutons, lettuce, Lemon-Grilled Chicken Breasts, and egg mixture in a large bowl. toss gently. Divide salad evenly among 4 plates. Sprinkle each serving with 1 tablespoon cheese.'),
('482', '1', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('482', '2', 'Remove white papery skin from garlic head (do not peel or separate the cloves). Wrap in foil.'),
('482', '3', 'Bake at 350 for 1 hour. cool 10 minutes. Separate cloves. squeeze to extract garlic pulp. Discard skins. Set aside 1 tablespoon garlic pulp. reserve remaining pulp for another use.'),
('482', '4', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('482', '5', 'Cut the red bell peppers in half lengthwise, and discard seeds and membranes.'),
('482', '6', 'Place pepper halves, skin sides up, on a foil-lined baking sheet. flatten with hand. Broil for 15 minutes or until blackened.'),
('482', '7', 'Place in a paper bag. fold to close tightly.'),
('482', '8', 'Let stand for 20 minutes. peel.'),
('482', '9', 'Combine bell peppers, reserved garlic, oil, and next 5 ingredients (through black pepper) in a food processor. process until smooth. Sprinkle with parsley.'),
('483', '1', 'Blend 1/4 cup tuna, anchovy, mayonnaise, oil, capers, and lemon juice in a blender until smooth to make tonnato sauce.'),
('483', '2', 'Pulse eggplant, garlic, parsley, zest, vinegar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a food processor until combined but not smooth.'),
('483', '3', 'Toss tomatoes with mint, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('483', '4', 'Divide eggplant mixture among jars and layer remaining tuna (broken up into large chunks), tonnato sauce, croutons, and tomatoes (including juices) on top.'),
('483', '5', 'Drizzle with olive oil.'),
('483', '6', 'Cooks'' note:Assembled jars can be chilled up to 6 hours.'),
('483', '7', 'Serve at room temperature.'),
('486', '1', 'In a large bowl, mix together the mayonnaise, anchovies, vinegar, and paprika. On a cutting board, use the flat side of a knife to mash together the garlic and salt until a paste forms (or use a mortar and pestle).'),
('486', '2', 'Add the paste to the bowl and toss to combine.'),
('486', '3', 'Mix in the eggs.'),
('486', '4', 'Divide the salad between 2 slices of bread, top with tomato, and sandwich with the remaining 2 bread slices.'),
('486', '5', 'Serve immediately.'),
('489', '1', 'Sprinkle the eggplant slices with salt and arrange in a single layer. Cover with kitchen weights or weighted plates and let sit for 2 hours.'),
('489', '2', 'Preheat the grill or broiler.'),
('489', '3', 'Brush eggplant slices with olive oil and grill for 10 minutes on each side or until dark brown.'),
('489', '4', 'Brush the pepper slices with olive oil and cook skin side down for 5 to 6 minutes, or until blackened and blistered.'),
('489', '5', 'Brush the zucchini slices with olive oil and grill for 5 minutes on each side or until grilled and cooked through.'),
('489', '6', 'In a small bowl, combine 1/4 cup olive oil, the vinegar, garlic, anchovies, and herbs, and mix well.'),
('489', '7', 'Pour the mixture over the hot vegetables and cover immediately with aluminum foil. Marinate overnight, covered but at room temperature.'),
('489', '8', 'Serve at room temperature.'),
('493', '1', 'In a blender, puree the silken tofu with the olive oil, lemon juice, the 1 1/2 tablespoons of Parmigiano, the anchovy, garlic, Worcestershire and mustard. season the dressing with salt and pepper.'),
('493', '2', 'Wrap the firm tofu in paper towels and press out some of the water. In a large skillet, heat 1/4 inch of vegetable oil until shimmering. In a bowl, toss the tofu with the cornstarch until coated.'),
('493', '3', 'Add the cubes to the oil and fry over moderately high heat, turning once, until crisp, about 8 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the croutons to a paper towellined plate. season with salt.'),
('493', '4', 'In a large bowl, toss the romaine with the dressing and two-thirds of the croutons.'),
('493', '5', 'Transfer the salad to plates and top with the remaining croutons. Sprinkle with Parmigiano and serve.'),
('494', '1', 'Whisk together eggs, milk, salt, and pepper, and pour into a shallow baking dish. Dredge sandwiches in flour, and shake off excess. Dip in egg mixture turning to coat on all sides.'),
('494', '2', 'Transfer to hot oil. Fry, turning occasionally, until golden on all sides.'),
('494', '3', 'Drain on a paper towel-lined baking sheet, and place in oven to keep warm.'),
('496', '1', 'Prick chiles 6-8 times with a small, sharp knife.'),
('496', '2', 'Heat a large frying pan over medium heat. add chiles and olive oil. Cook 5 minutes. Turn heat up to full whack. add garlic, parsley stalks, and anchovies, stirring constantly. When garlic starts to become golden, add tomatoes, and season with salt and pepper. bring mixture to a boil.'),
('496', '3', 'Add vodka, and reduce heat to simmer. Gently bash up chiles with a wooden spoon.'),
('496', '4', 'Cook pasta according to package directions. drain. Toss immediately with sauce.'),
('496', '5', 'Divide pasta evenly among bowls. Roughly chop reserved parsley leaves. sprinkle over pasta. Sprinkle lemon zest over pasta. squeeze in juice, catching pits in your hands.'),
('496', '6', 'Drizzle with extra-virgin olive oil, if desired. serve immediately with a salad.'),
('499', '1', 'To make dressing, process first 10 ingredients in a blender until smooth.'),
('499', '2', 'Arrange greens and tomatoes on a platter.'),
('499', '3', 'Serve with dressing.'),
('504', '1', 'Pre heat the oven to 450Lay the pastry sheet onto some parchment and roll out to get rid of the creases. Score a border around the edge and prick the pastry in the middle with a fork.');